00:00:29,854 --> 00:00:31,095
within the team I'm on.

11
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:37,202
Just briefly, I'm going to go over what EVE Online is, for

12
00:00:37,242 --> 00:00:38,343
those of you that may not be aware.

13
00:00:39,264 --> 00:00:42,307
So EVE Online is a sci-fi, MMO sandbox.

14
00:00:42,707 --> 00:00:44,569
The sandbox is a really key thing for us.

15
00:00:45,810 --> 00:00:48,652
And by that, I mean we stay very hands-off of our game.

16
00:00:48,752 --> 00:00:50,413
We provide our players with tools.

17
00:00:50,834 --> 00:00:53,096
What they do with those tools is entirely up to them.

18
00:00:53,596 --> 00:00:57,079
If you scam someone and you're using the tools provided in

19
00:00:57,099 --> 00:00:59,261
game, we will not intervene in that.

20
00:00:59,381 --> 00:01:01,623
So you can be scammed and that kind of stuff.

21
00:01:02,772 --> 00:01:05,953
Building on that, though, we are also a single sharded game.

22
00:01:06,673 --> 00:01:09,675
We have one cluster in London, which is where all of our

23
00:01:09,715 --> 00:01:10,695
players connect and play.

24
00:01:11,395 --> 00:01:13,776
And this tends to amplify the sandbox nature of our game.

25
00:01:13,996 --> 00:01:17,198
If you pull off a great heist, everyone in our game tends to

26
00:01:17,258 --> 00:01:17,818
hear about it.

27
00:01:17,858 --> 00:01:19,999
And it's this big thing because it happened on one

28
00:01:20,059 --> 00:01:21,199
server in one universe.

29
