We came out in 2003.

31
00:01:28,858 --> 00:01:30,099
And relevant to this presentation,

32
00:01:30,879 --> 00:01:32,741
we have generally an above-average

33
00:01:33,501 --> 00:01:34,422
technical user base.

34
00:01:34,482 --> 00:01:37,724
Our users tend to be more technically inclined than most.

35
00:01:40,086 --> 00:01:42,207
And then, as this will come into play a little bit later,

36
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:44,889
these are some numbers, averages from 2014

